summary: Radio Free Skaro #673 - The Way We Were
title: Radio Free Skaro #673 - The Way We Were
body:
Radio Free Skaro #673 - The Way We Were, in which we take a look back at our own history with #gally1, dating back to our first time attending the best convention on Earth in 2009!

The most wonderful time of the year for the Three Who Rule is upon us as the 30th edition of Gallifrey One is right around the corner. Before we look ahead to this year’s event next week with our annual Gallifrey One preview show, join us as we take a look back at the previous ten years of the convention and our experiences with it, and how the greatest Doctor Who convention on Earth has…

summary: as excited as I am for “Good Omens” coming out I’m still a bit miffed that Alexander Siddig wasn’t cast as Famine because he’s...
body:
as excited as I am for “Good Omens” coming out I’m still a bit miffed that Alexander Siddig wasn’t cast as Famine because he’s precisely how I pictured the character looking when I read the book (fangirling aside)

David Tennant being in it makes up for everything but honestly who wouldn’t pay to see Sid and David in a scene together - like, really, just once. I know I would.

title: The End of time
body:
Putting aside all of my feelings towards this two-parter which are sour for obvious reasons. 

I believe that The End of time part 2 is one of the best episodes of doctor who simply based on the performances of David Tennant and Bernard Cribbins. The two of them together made quite possibly the best duo I’ve ever seen and Tennants emotional and compelling ‘monologue’ at the end just after the time lords have been defeated really captures the pain that The Doctor feels.

Just decided to share that with you. Have a good day
